{
  "texts": [
    "By modeling the likelihood of cache hits and misses probabilistically, the method estimates execution time distributions.",
    "For example, the probability of a cache miss can be analyzed based on reuse distances, which is then used to estimate the WCET.",
    "Early works by Quinones et al. [57] and Cazorla et al.",
    "[58] provide initial methods for random replacement caches, which were later shown to be optimistic and unsound.",
    "Davis et al. [59] introduce accurate techniques based on reuse distances and cache contention, addressing earlier shortcomings."
  ]
}